tip.text: Japanese Matsuzaka was good but it's hard to mess up a great quality meat. The 45 dry aged rib eye is a great deal already and not as fatty as wagyu with lots of flavor. Needs more wine by the glass
Roasted quail was amaze balls. Really enjoyed pulled pork sandwich and beef short ribs as well. :-) worth the 1 1/2 hour table wait on a Friday night :-) love the open kitchen format
